                        <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                           <locus target="#286vab"/><foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈጸመ፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ሃይማኖት፡
                              ዘይነግር፡ ተዋሕዶተ፡ መለኮት <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/>፨ ወፍጻሜሁኒ፡ ኮነ፡ በ፷፻ወ፮፻፡ ፵ወ፮፡ ዓመተ፡ ዓለም፡ በዘመነ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡
                           በ፪፻፷ወ፪፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፨ እንዘ፡ አብቅቴ፡ ወርኀ፡ ፬፡ በ፳ወ፮፡ መጥቅዕ፨ ወእንዘ፡ አብቅቴ፡ ፀሐይ፡ ፯፨ እንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡
                           ፀሐይ፡ በሳድስ፡ ኆኅቱ፨ እም፡ ሐምስ፡ ኆኅት፡ በጊዜ፡ ግብአቱ፨ በ፫ዓመተ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ <del rend="erasure"/>፡ በጸጋ፡
                           እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘተሰምየ፡ ሥልጣን፡ ሰገድ፡ ወጳጳስሂ፡ አሜሃ፡ አቡነ፡ ስምዖን፨ ወካዕበ፡ ኮነ፡ ፍጻሜሁኒ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡
                           ሃይማኖት፡ አመ፡ ፭፡ ዘወርኃ፡ ጵዮን፨ በነገረ፡ ሱርስት፨ ወሮሜሂ፡ ሚጥርዮስ፨ ወበዕብራይስጥ፤ ሐዚራን፨ ወበግዕዝሂ፡ ሰኔ፨
                           ወዘአጽሐፎ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አባ፡ ዘክርስቶስ፡ መምህረ፡ ሕግ፡ ወሥርዓት፨ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ ተዝካረ፡ በምድር፡ ወበሰማያት፨
                           ወዘጸሐፎሂ፡ ወልዱ፡ መልክዐ፡ ክርስቶስ፨ እግዚአብሔር፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞሙ፡ ውስተ፡ ኢየሩሳሌም፡ ሰማያዊ፨ ምስለ፡ ሱታፌሁ፡ ጽጌ፡
                           ሐይማኖት፨ ወፈድፋደሰ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ዘክርስቶስ፡ ዘጻመወ፡ ለአጽሕፎ፡ በጥብዓተ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፨ ኢትርሥዕዎ፡ ወትረ፡ ኵልክሙ፡
                           ደቂቀ፡ ዳሞ፡ ዐቢይ፡ ወንኡስ፨ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፨</foreign>
                           <foreign xml:lang="en">This ‘Book of the Faith’, which talks about the union of divinity, was completed
                              with the help of God <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/>. And its completion happened in <date calendar="world" when-custom="6646" when="1154">6646  year of the world,</date>
                              in the year of Mark the Evangelist, in <date calendar="diocletian" when-custom="262" when="1610">262 year of mercy.</date> When the <foreign>ʾabqǝte</foreign> of the
                              month was 4 and the <foreign>maṭqǝʿ</foreign> was 26. And when the <foreign>ʾabqǝte</foreign> of the sun was 7; when the sun was at the 6th height; from the 5th height at the time of its rise. 
                              In the <date when="1610">3rd year</date> of reign of our King <del rend="erasure"/> by the grace of God who was called
                              <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Śǝlṭān Sagad</persName> and <persName ref="PRS8740Semon"><roleName type="function">Metropolitan</roleName> <roleName type="function">ʾAbuna</roleName>  Sǝmʿon</persName>. 
                              And again the completion of this ‘Book of the Faith’ happened on the 5th of the month <foreign xml:lang="syr">Ṗǝyon</foreign> in the Syriac
                              speech and in Roman <foreign xml:lang="la">Miṭrǝyos</foreign> and in Hebrew <foreign xml:lang="he">Hazirān</foreign> and in Gǝʿǝz <foreign xml:lang="gez">Sane</foreign>. 
                              And the one who commissioned this book was <persName ref="PRS14617Zakrestos" role="patron"><roleName type="title">ʾAbbā</roleName> Zakrǝstos</persName>, the teacher of law and
                              order, so that it might become memorial in earth and in heaven. And the one who
                              wrote it was his son <persName ref="PRS14616MalkeaKrestos" role="scribe">Malkǝʾa Krǝstos</persName>. May God write their names in Heavenly
                              Jerusalem; together with associate <persName ref="PRS14717SegeHaymanot">Ṣǝge Hāymānot</persName>; and particularly for
                              ʾabuna <persName ref="PRS14617Zakrestos" role="patron">Zakrǝstos</persName>who took the trouble to commission it in perseverance of flesh and soul.
                              May thou never forget all the children of <placeName ref="INS0105DD">Dāmmo</placeName>, the great and the minor. Forever and ever, Amen. </foreign>
                           <note>The colophon mentions the regnal name of <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"><roleName type="title">King</roleName> Śǝlṭān Sagad I</persName>
                              (the King’s ‘worldly’ name, Susǝnyos, is erased) as well as the names of <persName ref="PRS8740Semon"><roleName type="function">Metropolitan</roleName> <roleName type="function">ʾAbuna</roleName>  Sǝmʿon</persName> (in tenure <date>1607–1617</date>), 
                              the commissioner <persName ref="PRS14617Zakrestos" role="patron"><roleName type="title">ʾAbbā</roleName> Zakrǝstos</persName>, <persName ref="PRS14616MalkeaKrestos" role="scribe">Malkǝʾa Krǝstos</persName> 
                              and his companion <persName ref="PRS14717SegeHaymanot">Ṣǝge Hāymānot</persName>.
                              For the completion of the manuscript the dates mentioned are <date calendar="world" when-custom="6646" when="1154">6646 year of the
                                 world</date>, <date calendar="diocletian" when-custom="262" when="1610">262 year of mercy</date> and the <date when="1610">3rd year</date> of the reign of
                              <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos, i.e., Śǝlṭān Sagad</persName>, that is in 1610 CE. There is a discrepancy between the year of the world, which gives 1154 CE, on the one hand, and the year of mercy and the 3rd year of the reign 
